Title:          Iconicity in the lab: a review of behavioral, developmental, and neuroimaging research into sound-symbolism
Subject:        This review covers experimental approaches to sound-symbolism--from infants to adults, and from Sapir's foundational studies to twenty-first century product naming.
Keywords:       iconicity, sound-symbolism, neuroimaging, psycholinguistics, linguistics, ideophones, synesthesia, cross-modal correspondence
